## Africana Studies Relation

Billy Strayhorn’s contributions to jazz and African-American culture make him a pivotal figure in Africana Studies. His work provides insight into the intersection of race, art, and identity, offering valuable perspectives on the cultural contributions of Black musicians in 20th-century America.

